column5: Hay all I got this in an e-mail from a friend of mine.        Jose
pretty amazing isn't it.  TJ posted these about a week ago, but I still like looking at it!
Hey, hahah Travor Caron posted these pics... Do you know him ?
Is this here in Ontario or in Newfoundland? There are a lot of albino moose on the rock.  Curt

Did a little fishing this past summer near a town called Foleyet in northern Ontario and there is a small bar in the town with a "white" moose head on the wall. It got hit by a train a couple miles out of town. There is also several pics of these white moose in the bar as well . The locals in the bar told me that these moose inhabit this area of Ontario . Foleyet is a small railway town 100 km west of Timmins. Cheers Dave
If I didn't know how tasty Moose were I don't think I could shoot it.
